<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 12 at 11:14PM CST  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Beaver
County through MIDNIGHT CST...
At 1114 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles east of Elmwood, or 15 miles southeast of Beaver, moving north
at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Gate and Knowles.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CST for the Panhandle
of Oklahoma.</instruction>
